WEBVTT

00:01.401 --> 00:03.535
<i> Previously on</i>
<i> "women of the movement"...</i>

00:03.621 --> 00:04.570
Ollie: They think they found
emmett -- his body.

00:04.655 --> 00:05.654
Dr. Otken: I've never seen
such damage

00:05.740 --> 00:07.272
in such a short amount of time.

00:07.375 --> 00:09.808
Honestly don't see any use for
an autopsy.

00:09.910 --> 00:14.079
This whole thing is a hoax
cooked up by the naacp.

00:14.165 --> 00:16.131
The photo of that boy
when he's alive?

00:16.250 --> 00:17.883
Don't look like nothing
I saw.

00:17.968 --> 00:20.552
The defense is running
with strider's hoax theory,

00:20.638 --> 00:22.788
but a mother's testimony
means something

00:22.890 --> 00:24.089
in a southern courtroom.

00:24.175 --> 00:25.791
Before those men
killed that boy,

00:25.893 --> 00:28.727
some field hands saw him riding
in the back of a pickup truck,

00:28.813 --> 00:30.512
sitting between two negro men.

00:30.598 --> 00:32.147
If we can track them down,
maybe we can tie

00:32.266 --> 00:34.183
bryant and milam directly to
the murder.

00:34.268 --> 00:37.936
All I saw was a truck parked
over at the shed that morning.

00:38.022 --> 00:39.137
You recognize any of
those men?

00:39.240 --> 00:43.075
But one of them was tall
and was kind of bald-headed.

00:43.160 --> 00:44.693
Willie reed.
I heard you know something

00:44.779 --> 00:46.161
about that chicago boy.

00:46.280 --> 00:47.413
I think I seen him.

00:47.498 --> 00:48.864
You know, on the back
of some truck.

00:48.949 --> 00:51.316
You heard about that third man?
Goes by too tight.

00:51.419 --> 00:53.619
He's missing?
He worked for
one of them milam brothers.

00:53.704 --> 00:56.255
How do you respond to
local citizens who say,

00:56.340 --> 00:58.990
"a civilized mother would never
have put a child's body

00:59.093 --> 01:00.325
on public display?"

01:00.428 --> 01:03.679
opening my son's casket
made it impossible to ignore

01:03.798 --> 01:05.464
what really goes on down here.

01:05.549 --> 01:06.348
[ gunshots ]

01:06.467 --> 01:07.883
[ laughter ]

01:07.968 --> 01:11.053
there's quite a bit
being said about you,

01:11.138 --> 01:14.523
and I think it's time
we heard your side.

01:14.642 --> 01:16.058
♪♪

01:16.177 --> 01:19.061
[ eartha kitt's "if I was a boy"
plays ]

01:19.146 --> 01:21.346
♪♪

01:21.449 --> 01:22.698
<i> ♪ if I was a boy ♪</i>

01:22.817 --> 01:25.984
<i> ♪ I'd know the things</i>
<i> a girl shouldn't know ♪</i>

01:26.070 --> 01:28.186
<i> ♪ I'd go where girls</i>
<i> shouldn't go ♪</i>

01:28.289 --> 01:29.571
<i> ♪ so, oh ♪</i>

01:29.657 --> 01:30.739
[ sighs ]

01:30.825 --> 01:32.124
♪<i> so ♪</i>

01:32.209 --> 01:33.575
<i> ♪ if I was a boy ♪</i>

01:33.661 --> 01:35.711
what's the hold up?

01:35.830 --> 01:37.195
I just wish I had
something to wear

01:37.298 --> 01:39.081
that was worth
looking at.

01:39.166 --> 01:42.251
What about
this one here?

01:42.336 --> 01:44.202
It's fine,
I suppose.

01:44.305 --> 01:47.306
Except I've worn it
once already to court.

01:47.391 --> 01:49.842
<i> ♪ I'd pack and catch me</i>
<i> a train ♪</i>

01:49.927 --> 01:53.545
<i> ♪ go out and raise me</i>
<i> some cain ♪</i>

01:53.647 --> 01:54.813
<i> ♪ if I was a boy ♪</i>

01:54.899 --> 01:57.599
they sure dress different
up north, don't they?

01:57.685 --> 02:00.552
They talk different,
too.

02:00.654 --> 02:04.222
What she wears and how she talks
is none of your concern.

02:04.325 --> 02:09.661
<i> ♪ there is such a lot a girl</i>
<i> has gotta cope with ♪</i>

02:09.747 --> 02:10.746
<i> ♪ there are times</i>
<i> I think ♪</i>

02:10.865 --> 02:12.230
I expect the press will be
after me today,

02:12.333 --> 02:14.449
once I testify.

02:14.535 --> 02:18.236
Lord, I wish they'd
just leave us alone.

02:18.339 --> 02:20.205
Juanita: I suppose I don't need
to remind you

02:20.291 --> 02:21.874
that this ain't another one
of your high school

02:21.959 --> 02:23.709
beauty pageants.

02:23.794 --> 02:27.296
Roy's life is on the line,
and so is j.W.'s.

02:27.381 --> 02:31.082
For heaven's sake, juanita,
you don't think I know it?

02:31.185 --> 02:32.751
[ child screams in distance ]

02:32.853 --> 02:34.303
I'll deal with him.

02:34.388 --> 02:37.139
You need to hurry up
and get your head on straight.

02:37.224 --> 02:40.225
You got us all
into this mess.

02:40.327 --> 02:42.227
It's up to you
to get us out.

02:42.313 --> 02:43.445
[ paper slaps ]

02:43.564 --> 02:47.199
♪♪

02:47.284 --> 02:49.034
chatham: The defense is
desperate, mrs. Bradley.

02:49.119 --> 02:50.536
I can smell it.

02:50.621 --> 02:52.871
We have kidnapping confessions
from both defendants,

02:52.957 --> 02:55.207
a great deal
of circumstantial evidence,

02:55.242 --> 02:57.576
and now, thanks to
these new witnesses,

02:57.611 --> 02:59.378
we can place emmett
at the plantation

02:59.413 --> 03:00.946
where milam's own brother
worked

03:00.981 --> 03:03.115
a few hours after
his disappearance.

03:03.150 --> 03:04.783
Thank god for dr. Howard
and his team.

03:04.818 --> 03:07.119
[ sighs ]
you can bet we did.

03:07.154 --> 03:08.654
Before these witnesses
came forward,

03:08.689 --> 03:11.089
we had no clue
where the crime was committed,

03:11.158 --> 03:12.757
only that it was.

03:12.776 --> 03:16.295
And today, I intend to prove
that bryant and milam

03:16.330 --> 03:18.430
killed your son
on that very plantation

03:18.465 --> 03:19.798
that same morning.

03:19.867 --> 03:21.266
It's gonna be tough
for a jury to ignore

03:21.302 --> 03:23.435
eye-witness testimony
from these farmhands, ma'am.

03:23.504 --> 03:24.770
I'm glad to hear that.

03:24.805 --> 03:29.775
However...
The fact remains

03:29.810 --> 03:31.910
that our only shred
of physical evidence --

03:31.946 --> 03:35.614
our only proof that
a murder occurred --

03:35.683 --> 03:37.649
is your son's body.

03:37.685 --> 03:40.953
Which is why they are so
determined to deny his identity.

03:40.988 --> 03:44.089
And why we need you
to prove to the jury

03:44.124 --> 03:47.359
that there was no hoax,
and that, as a mother,

03:47.394 --> 03:50.395
you would know
your son better than anyone.

03:50.431 --> 03:52.364
I understand.

03:52.399 --> 03:54.866
You need me
to tell the truth.

03:54.969 --> 03:57.202
And that's exactly
what I intend to do.

03:57.304 --> 03:59.588
The defense will try to cast
doubts, of course,

03:59.673 --> 04:02.874
but just stick to the facts
and you'll do fine.

04:02.977 --> 04:08.380
Now, um,
there is one more thing.

04:08.482 --> 04:12.100
We've received a few letters
from concerned citizens

04:12.186 --> 04:13.769
who haven't taken kindly
to the fact

04:13.854 --> 04:16.855
that I've referred to you
in the press as "mrs. Bradley."

04:16.941 --> 04:20.275
I'm sure you're aware
of the southern custom?

04:20.361 --> 04:21.493
I am.

04:21.578 --> 04:23.495
We believe it would not
serve us well

04:23.580 --> 04:24.913
to risk offending the jury

04:25.032 --> 04:28.133
before they've even had
a chance to hear you speak.

04:28.202 --> 04:30.252
If you'll permit me,
I suggest

04:30.371 --> 04:34.139
I stick to the custom
during questioning.

04:34.241 --> 04:36.174
You're welcome to
call me mamie.

04:36.260 --> 04:37.676
Thank you.

04:37.778 --> 04:44.149
And please take care
with your responses, too.

04:44.251 --> 04:46.818
They're going to want
to hear you say "sir."

04:50.958 --> 04:53.024
vendor: Pop!
Get your ice cold soda pop.

04:53.127 --> 04:56.027
[ tense music plays ]

04:56.130 --> 04:59.030
[ indistinct conversations ]

04:59.133 --> 05:03.302
♪♪

05:03.387 --> 05:04.720
[ smooches ]

05:04.838 --> 05:06.305
♪♪

05:06.390 --> 05:09.141
good morning.

05:09.226 --> 05:10.759
Look at you.

05:10.844 --> 05:11.760
Almost didn't recognize you

05:11.845 --> 05:14.346
with all that paint
on your face.

05:15.432 --> 05:16.348
[ chuckles ]
soda pop!

05:16.433 --> 05:18.100
Ice cold soda pop.

05:18.185 --> 05:19.685
Milam: Damn,
it just gets hotter

05:19.770 --> 05:21.103
in this hell hole every day,
doesn't it?

05:21.188 --> 05:22.738
Son. Gimme a couple of them
cold ones.

05:22.856 --> 05:24.356
Keep 'em coming.

05:24.441 --> 05:27.359
[ indistinct conversations ]

05:27.444 --> 05:34.449
♪♪

05:34.535 --> 05:37.452
you straight on
what you're saying?

05:37.538 --> 05:39.204
Of course, roy.

05:39.289 --> 05:47.679
♪♪

05:47.765 --> 05:56.104
♪♪

05:56.223 --> 05:58.023
[ clanging ]

05:58.125 --> 06:06.031
♪♪

06:06.116 --> 06:14.039
♪♪

06:14.124 --> 06:21.997
♪♪

06:22.082 --> 06:30.005
♪♪

06:30.090 --> 06:38.013
♪♪

06:38.098 --> 06:41.016
-- captions by vitac --

06:41.101 --> 06:43.985
♪♪

06:44.104 --> 06:47.072
chatham: Now, mandy,
I direct your attention

06:47.157 --> 06:50.742
to the 28th day
of August, 1955.

06:50.828 --> 06:53.278
Did you see willie reed
that morning?

06:55.783 --> 06:57.833
Yes, sir.

06:57.951 --> 07:01.169
He stopped by my house
about, uh --

07:01.288 --> 07:05.323
well, along 6:30,
7 o'clock.

07:05.426 --> 07:07.992
And at that time,
did you look out

07:08.095 --> 07:11.162
towards mr. Leslie milam's
house?

07:11.265 --> 07:13.164
Y-yes, sir.
I looked out the window.

07:13.267 --> 07:14.382
[whispering] what the hell
happened to our chairs?

07:14.468 --> 07:16.685
Ruby: [whispering] shh!
Somebody must have moved them.

07:16.804 --> 07:17.769
Shh.

07:17.855 --> 07:19.387
Judge swango:
I need order, please.

07:19.506 --> 07:21.857
I understand our audience
has grown today,

07:21.975 --> 07:23.475
but I cannot allow anyone
in those aisles

07:23.560 --> 07:27.028
because it poses
a fire hazard.

07:27.147 --> 07:28.346
I'm sorry, but if you do not
have a seat,

07:28.449 --> 07:30.065
you'll have to wait outside.

07:40.461 --> 07:42.828
Better luck next time,
boys.

07:44.164 --> 07:45.797
You may proceed.

07:49.586 --> 07:52.704
Now, what did you see
when you looked out

07:52.806 --> 07:56.091
towards mr. Leslie milam's
house, mandy?

07:57.511 --> 08:01.847
I saw a green and white truck
out there,

08:01.932 --> 08:04.349
and four white men.

08:04.434 --> 08:05.767
They were going in and out
the shed,

08:05.853 --> 08:09.754
and one went to the well
and got a drink of water

08:09.857 --> 08:11.556
and then back
to the shed.

08:11.658 --> 08:15.193
Would you recognize that man
if you saw him again?

08:15.279 --> 08:18.196
[ suspenseful music plays ]

08:18.282 --> 08:21.950
♪♪

08:22.035 --> 08:24.503
yes.

08:24.588 --> 08:28.573
He was kind of a tall man.

08:28.675 --> 08:30.342
And bald-headed.

08:30.427 --> 08:36.548
♪♪

08:36.633 --> 08:38.383
thank you, mandy.

08:38.468 --> 08:40.218
Hicks: Three days trying to
track those witnesses down

08:40.304 --> 08:42.721
and now we can't even report
on what they say?

08:42.806 --> 08:44.389
Well, the drug store's been
selling folding chairs.

08:44.474 --> 08:46.274
I've seen a few white reporters
bringing them in.

08:46.393 --> 08:48.059
And you think they're going to
let us get away with that, too?

08:48.145 --> 08:49.093
Never know
unless you try.

08:49.196 --> 08:50.979
Excuse me.

08:51.064 --> 08:52.898
You're a reporter,
aren't ya?

08:52.983 --> 08:55.116
Trying to be.
[ sighs ]

08:55.235 --> 08:57.619
what can I do for you?

08:57.738 --> 08:59.571
Well, we've been out here
hoping to find somebody

08:59.656 --> 09:01.272
that could help us.

09:01.375 --> 09:02.991
You see, m--

09:04.795 --> 09:07.111
you see, my wife,
she heard some talk yesterday

09:07.214 --> 09:09.280
while she was getting
her hair done.

09:09.383 --> 09:11.833
And we thought somebody
ought to know about it.

09:11.919 --> 09:13.335
What did you hear?

09:13.420 --> 09:16.004
Well, it's about them men
folks have been talking about.

09:16.089 --> 09:18.173
The ones that were
in the truck the night

09:18.258 --> 09:20.058
they got
that chicago boy.

09:20.143 --> 09:22.644
[ birds chirping ]

09:23.931 --> 09:26.131
chatham: Willie,
as you came up

09:26.233 --> 09:28.066
towards mr. Leslie milam's
house,

09:28.151 --> 09:29.401
did you see anyone there?

09:29.486 --> 09:31.903
N-no, sir,
not at first.

09:32.005 --> 09:35.640
But there was
a green a-and white truck

09:35.742 --> 09:39.411
in front of the shed,
and it was the same truck

09:39.496 --> 09:42.364
I had seen earlier
that had passed me by.

09:42.449 --> 09:43.915
Who was in
that truck then?

09:44.001 --> 09:46.585
Four white men
in the cab,

09:46.670 --> 09:49.004
um, and three colored men
in the back,

09:49.122 --> 09:52.674
and I seen somebody
sitting down

09:52.793 --> 09:55.594
in the bed of the truck --
a colored boy.

09:55.696 --> 09:58.213
Hmm.
Now, later on,

09:58.298 --> 10:00.432
did you recognize
a photograph

10:00.517 --> 10:02.000
or anything that indicated
to you

10:02.102 --> 10:05.637
who was sitting down
in the bed of that truck?

10:05.722 --> 10:10.942
When I looked at the newspaper,
um, I seen a photo of a boy.

10:11.028 --> 10:15.647
It was the same one I seen
in the back of the truck.

10:15.732 --> 10:18.733
And was that emmett till?

10:18.819 --> 10:20.568
Well --
we object, your honor.

10:20.654 --> 10:22.203
Judge swango:
Objection is sustained

10:22.322 --> 10:25.407
unless it's connected,
of course.

10:25.492 --> 10:30.962
Now, I have a picture here
that was offered as exhibit 1.

10:31.048 --> 10:33.865
Have you ever seen
this boy before?

10:33.967 --> 10:36.200
Yes, sir.
It is a picture of the boy

10:36.303 --> 10:39.421
I seen on the back of
the truck.

10:39.506 --> 10:43.041
Now, as you were passing by
mr. Leslie milam's place

10:43.143 --> 10:48.546
later that morning,
was mr. J.W. Milam there?

10:48.649 --> 10:49.714
Yes, sir.

10:49.816 --> 10:52.350
I-I seen him come out
of the shed to the well.

10:52.436 --> 10:55.403
Mr. J.W. Milam, the man that is
sitting right over there?

10:55.522 --> 10:56.421
Yes, sir.

10:56.523 --> 10:57.889
Will you state

10:57.991 --> 11:02.393
whether he had
anything unusual

11:02.496 --> 11:04.996
on his person?

11:05.082 --> 11:06.898
He had a pistol
on his belt.

11:07.000 --> 11:12.120
And what did mr. J.W. Milam do
when you saw him?

11:12.205 --> 11:13.588
Well, he, um --

11:13.707 --> 11:16.541
he just went to the well,
got a drink of water,

11:16.626 --> 11:19.761
and then -- and then
went back towards the shed.

11:19.880 --> 11:21.296
And after you passed
the shed,

11:21.381 --> 11:31.589
did you hear
or see anything unusual?

11:31.692 --> 11:33.257
[ clears throat ]

11:33.360 --> 11:38.613
I heard somebody hollering
from in there,

11:38.732 --> 11:41.483
and I heard some licks
like --

11:41.568 --> 11:43.868
like somebody
was whipping somebody.

11:46.156 --> 11:47.405
Thank you.

11:48.909 --> 11:50.575
No further questions.

11:53.296 --> 11:54.746
Willie... [ clears throat ]

11:54.831 --> 11:57.782
when that truck passed
by you that morning,

11:57.884 --> 12:01.970
did you recognize
mr. J.W. Milam in there?

12:02.089 --> 12:04.305
Well, I-I didn't pay
too much attention

12:04.424 --> 12:05.807
to them in--
inside the truck.

12:05.926 --> 12:07.842
I-I just looked at the ones
in the back.

12:07.928 --> 12:12.931
Then you wouldn't say that
mr. Milam was inside the truck?

12:13.016 --> 12:14.015
No, sir,
I wouldn't say that.

12:14.101 --> 12:16.735
No. Later on,
when you passed this shed,

12:16.820 --> 12:18.403
how far were you from it?

12:18.488 --> 12:20.605
Yeah.
I wasn't too far, sir.

12:20.707 --> 12:23.474
Well, would you say
it was, um, 100 yards away?

12:23.577 --> 12:24.976
I wouldn't know, sir.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.111
Mm.

12:26.196 --> 12:28.113
Now, this person
you testified, uh,

12:28.198 --> 12:31.499
was mr. Milam, how, uh --

12:31.618 --> 12:35.336
how far was he from you
when you first saw him there?

12:37.657 --> 12:38.823
[ gulps ]

12:38.859 --> 12:43.361
well, I wouldn't say how far,
just because I --

12:43.396 --> 12:44.829
I just wouldn't know, sir.

12:44.848 --> 12:48.533
Then you don't know whether
you were 100 yards away,

12:48.568 --> 12:52.170
or 200 yards,
or 500 yards

12:52.272 --> 12:54.506
away from him?

12:54.574 --> 12:55.773
No -- no, sir.

12:55.792 --> 12:57.242
You, uh --
you stated that you heard

12:57.277 --> 12:59.644
something that sounded
like licks from inside the shed,

12:59.679 --> 13:01.679
but you don't know
whether mr. Milam

13:01.715 --> 13:04.482
was in there or not,
do you?

13:04.551 --> 13:06.684
But I-I seen mr. Milam,

13:06.720 --> 13:07.852
uh, when --
when he left the shed.

13:07.888 --> 13:12.023
But you didn't see him
in the shed, did you?

13:12.058 --> 13:13.191
Well, no, sir.

13:13.226 --> 13:16.361
But I-I seen him
w-when he left the shed and --

13:16.396 --> 13:18.530
and went to the well,

13:18.565 --> 13:21.266
a-and I seen him
when he went back towards it.

13:21.301 --> 13:23.401
But you don't know whether
the sounds you heard

13:23.470 --> 13:25.503
was somebody hammering,

13:25.539 --> 13:27.772
trying to fix a wagon,
or something like that.

13:27.808 --> 13:30.208
It was somebody
whipping somebody.

13:30.243 --> 13:31.810
S-sir.

13:34.881 --> 13:37.182
[ sighs ]

13:37.217 --> 13:40.602
um, your honor, so,
we ask the court

13:40.720 --> 13:44.973
to exclude all evidence
as offered by this witness

13:45.058 --> 13:49.093
and to direct the jury
to wholly disregard it,

13:49.196 --> 13:53.198
because roy bryant has
not been identified in any way

13:53.283 --> 13:57.101
as being present on the occasion
as testified by this witness.

13:57.204 --> 13:59.287
Your honor,
the defendants had the right

13:59.406 --> 14:00.872
to be tried separately,

14:00.957 --> 14:06.110
but they chose
to stand trial together.

14:06.213 --> 14:07.912
The motion will be overruled.

14:07.998 --> 14:10.548
The testimony stands.

14:10.634 --> 14:12.250
You may step down.

14:13.887 --> 14:19.591
♪♪

14:19.676 --> 14:22.260
the state calls mamie bradley
next.

14:22.345 --> 14:23.961
♪♪

14:24.064 --> 14:25.146
[ door opens ]

14:25.265 --> 14:26.231
[ crowd murmuring ]

14:26.316 --> 14:28.266
[ gavel bangs ]

14:28.351 --> 14:31.269
[ solemn music plays ]

14:31.354 --> 14:35.106
♪♪

14:38.278 --> 14:39.444
damn it. Sold out.
Listen.

14:39.529 --> 14:41.145
Ain't they got any more chairs
in this godforsaken town?

14:41.248 --> 14:43.531
You know about those missing men
I heard about at the dance hall?

14:43.617 --> 14:46.501
They were spotted yesterday,
about 20 miles up the road

14:46.620 --> 14:49.203
in the charleston...Jail.
[ panting ]

14:49.289 --> 14:51.673
wait.
Hold on...

14:51.791 --> 14:52.957
We gave their names
to chatham

14:53.043 --> 14:54.842
so they could be
brought in to testify,

14:54.961 --> 14:56.661
and you're telling me
they ended up in jail?

14:56.763 --> 14:59.514
Charleston jail is in
sheriff strider's jurisdiction,

14:59.633 --> 15:01.332
and we know
he's crooked as hell.

15:01.434 --> 15:02.300
What if he's got them
hidden away in there

15:02.385 --> 15:03.768
so chatham
can't find them?

15:03.853 --> 15:06.387
Well, the state wraps
up testimony today.

15:06.473 --> 15:08.172
Once they rest, it's over.

15:08.275 --> 15:10.441
We can't introduce
more witnesses.

15:10.527 --> 15:11.976
Well, I doubt the folks
at the jail would appreciate

15:12.062 --> 15:13.945
the likes of us just waltzing
in there to ask questions.

15:14.030 --> 15:16.230
Well, then we better find
another way to prove it.

15:16.316 --> 15:19.233
[ tense music plays ]

15:19.319 --> 15:26.157
♪♪

15:26.242 --> 15:28.242
hi. Excuse me,
can you tell me

15:28.328 --> 15:30.027
how to get to the jail
over in charleston?

15:30.130 --> 15:31.696
♪♪

15:31.798 --> 15:33.998
what kind of business
you got down there?

15:34.084 --> 15:35.300
I'm a reporter.

15:35.385 --> 15:37.635
Uh, dan wakefield -- I-I write
for<i> the nation.</i>

15:37.721 --> 15:39.754
Just following up
on a tip.

15:39.839 --> 15:42.140
Wondering if there was a --
a bus or some way

15:42.225 --> 15:43.808
to get out there?
[ laughs nervously ]

15:43.893 --> 15:47.211
♪♪

15:47.314 --> 15:48.713
tell you what.

15:48.815 --> 15:51.349
We was fixing to head
out there ourselves.

15:51.434 --> 15:53.050
Why don't you hitch
along with us?

15:53.153 --> 15:55.069
♪♪

15:55.188 --> 15:59.273
now, mamie, will you please
state for the court and jury

15:59.359 --> 16:01.609
whether you were able
to identify the body

16:01.695 --> 16:04.579
you saw at the funeral home
in chicago?

16:04.698 --> 16:05.913
Yes, sir.

16:06.032 --> 16:10.868
I positively identified the body
as being that of my son,

16:10.954 --> 16:14.455
emmett louis till.

16:14.541 --> 16:20.745
Please tell the court and
the jury how you looked at it

16:20.847 --> 16:24.081
and what you did
in identifying it.

16:24.184 --> 16:28.686
I looked at the face
very carefully.

16:28.722 --> 16:33.491
I looked at the ears
and the forehead

16:33.526 --> 16:37.428
and the hairline
and also the hair.

16:37.464 --> 16:42.500
And I looked at the nose
and the lips and his chin.

16:42.535 --> 16:44.736
I just looked at it
all over very thoroughly.

16:44.771 --> 16:47.572
And I knew, definitely,
that was my boy,

16:47.607 --> 16:50.008
beyond a shadow
of a doubt.

16:50.043 --> 16:53.244
Mamie, when your husband,
the father of emmett till,

16:53.279 --> 16:56.080
was killed overseas,
were his effects sent to you?

16:56.115 --> 16:57.415
Yes, sir.
They were.

16:57.450 --> 17:00.301
I'd like ask you if in those
effects there was a ring?

17:00.420 --> 17:02.253
Yes, sir --
now, your honor.

17:02.338 --> 17:04.756
We now object to the testimony
of this witness

17:04.841 --> 17:07.842
with reference to the effects,
or what is purported to be

17:07.927 --> 17:10.428
the effects of her dead husband
being sent to her,

17:10.513 --> 17:12.096
without showing just who,
when, and how

17:12.182 --> 17:14.348
those effects were sent.

17:14.434 --> 17:16.467
Yes, I believe there would
have to be a prior connection

17:16.569 --> 17:18.269
to identification
of the ring.

17:18.354 --> 17:19.487
Sustained.

17:19.606 --> 17:21.639
Your honor, we're just trying
to identify the ring

17:21.741 --> 17:23.074
that the boy had on.

17:23.159 --> 17:26.160
You can proceed
a little differently, I believe.

17:26.279 --> 17:27.612
Yes, sir.

17:29.833 --> 17:32.650
Mamie, I will ask you
if your son had a ring

17:32.752 --> 17:34.368
and frequently wore a ring

17:34.454 --> 17:36.921
and if that was sent to you
along with the effects

17:37.006 --> 17:38.706
of your husband that you got?

17:38.792 --> 17:40.842
Yes, sir.
We object to that,
your honor,

17:40.960 --> 17:43.127
for the reason that she said
the effects were sent to her

17:43.213 --> 17:45.680
that were supposed to belong
to her dead husband,

17:45.799 --> 17:47.215
but it hasn't been shown
in evidence

17:47.300 --> 17:49.350
anything about the identity
of these effects.

17:49.469 --> 17:51.102
The objection
is overruled.

17:54.858 --> 17:57.525
[ sighs ]

17:58.311 --> 18:01.846
I will now hand you
this ring, mamie,

18:01.948 --> 18:05.533
with an engraving on it,
"may 25, 1943,"

18:05.652 --> 18:07.318
and the large initials
of "l.T.,"

18:07.403 --> 18:09.620
and I will ask you
if this ring was sent along

18:09.706 --> 18:11.372
with the effects
purported to be

18:11.491 --> 18:12.857
the effects
of your dead husband?

18:12.909 --> 18:13.808
Yes, sir.

18:13.843 --> 18:15.293
What was
your husband's name?

18:15.361 --> 18:16.427
Louis till.

18:16.463 --> 18:18.830
In other words,
his initials were "l.T."?

18:18.898 --> 18:19.997
Yes, sir.

18:20.033 --> 18:21.599
And when you got that ring
in his effects,

18:21.634 --> 18:23.367
what happened to it?

18:23.403 --> 18:26.304
Uh, well, I kept the ring
in a jewelry box.

18:26.339 --> 18:28.639
Before he left for
mississippi,

18:28.675 --> 18:32.677
emmett looked in this jewelry
box to get, um, cuff links,

18:32.712 --> 18:34.846
I think it was, and when
he looked in the box there,

18:34.914 --> 18:36.047
he saw this ring.

18:36.082 --> 18:37.615
And he left chicago with it,
did he?

18:37.684 --> 18:38.783
Yes, sir.

18:38.818 --> 18:40.084
And you definitely saw that
that was the ring

18:40.120 --> 18:41.519
that he left there with?
Yes, sir.

18:41.554 --> 18:43.221
And that was the ring
that he had on him

18:43.256 --> 18:44.622
when he came down here
to mississippi?

18:44.691 --> 18:46.157
Yes, sir.

18:54.601 --> 19:00.972
Now, mamie, I have here
some photos

19:01.057 --> 19:04.859
taken by the police photographer
shortly after the body

19:04.978 --> 19:08.345
was removed
from the tallahatchie river.

19:08.448 --> 19:11.348
[ solemn music plays ]

19:11.451 --> 19:16.871
♪♪

19:16.990 --> 19:21.242
is that a picture of your son,
emmett till?

19:21.327 --> 19:27.882
♪♪

19:28.001 --> 19:30.751
yes, sir.
It is.

19:30.837 --> 19:32.369
Thank you, mamie.

19:32.472 --> 19:40.895
♪♪

19:41.014 --> 19:49.437
♪♪

19:49.522 --> 19:52.440
[ crying ]

19:52.525 --> 20:06.220
♪♪
mamie, did you have any life
insurance out on emmett till?

20:06.306 --> 20:08.589
We object, your honor.

20:09.842 --> 20:11.893
I'm gonna overrule that.

20:11.978 --> 20:15.096
Did you have
any life insurance on him?

20:15.181 --> 20:16.463
Yes, sir.

20:16.566 --> 20:18.816
How much insurance
did you have?

20:18.935 --> 20:20.701
About $400.

20:20.803 --> 20:22.536
And how long
had you had these, uh --

20:22.605 --> 20:25.273
these policies out on him?

20:25.358 --> 20:26.824
Almost from his birth.

20:26.943 --> 20:28.492
And to whom
were they payable?

20:28.611 --> 20:30.111
We object to that,
your honor.

20:30.213 --> 20:33.314
The objection is overruled.

20:33.416 --> 20:35.383
I was the beneficiary of one
of them

20:35.485 --> 20:37.501
and my mother
was of the other.

20:37.620 --> 20:39.987
And, uh -- and have you
tried to collect on --

20:40.089 --> 20:41.589
on those, uh,
payments yet?

20:41.674 --> 20:42.924
We object to that,
your honor.

20:43.009 --> 20:44.208
That is highly irrelevant.

20:44.294 --> 20:46.794
The objection
is overruled.

20:46.879 --> 20:50.831
Have you contacted the insurance
companies about collecting?

20:50.934 --> 20:54.352
Yes, sir.

20:54.470 --> 20:56.304
Now, [clears throat]

20:56.389 --> 21:00.007
was, uh, emmett ever
in any trouble up in chicago?

21:00.109 --> 21:02.109
We object to that,
your honor. Relevance.

21:02.195 --> 21:03.811
Judge swango:
The objection is sustained.

21:06.149 --> 21:08.366
You said you discussed
your son's trip down

21:08.484 --> 21:10.151
to mississippi
several times with him

21:10.236 --> 21:13.520
before he left chicago,
is that correct?

21:13.623 --> 21:14.739
Yes, sir.

21:14.824 --> 21:17.024
And did you caution him
how to conduct himself

21:17.126 --> 21:19.210
while he was down here
in mississippi before he left?

21:19.329 --> 21:20.411
Again -- relevance?

21:20.496 --> 21:21.712
I'll tell you
how it's relevant.

21:21.831 --> 21:25.199
I have an exhibit that I want
the witness to identify.

21:25.301 --> 21:27.134
Your honor, I think
it's perfectly clear

21:27.220 --> 21:28.302
what he is trying to do,

21:28.388 --> 21:30.054
and I think counsel
should be counseled

21:30.173 --> 21:32.306
to stop asking
more questions like that.

21:32.392 --> 21:33.808
The objection
is sustained.

21:33.893 --> 21:35.542
The court would like to ask
the gentlemen of the jury

21:35.645 --> 21:37.345
to step into the jury room
for a moment,

21:37.430 --> 21:39.313
so that we may discuss
this further.

21:41.434 --> 21:43.484
[ chairs sliding ]

21:45.071 --> 21:46.387
[ door opens ]

21:46.489 --> 21:49.106
[ crowd murmuring ]

22:01.087 --> 22:02.536
the court will allow
the defense counsel

22:02.622 --> 22:04.372
to proceed
with this line of questioning

22:04.457 --> 22:06.257
without the presence
of the jury.

22:06.376 --> 22:09.176
If counsel can show that the
testimony is indeed relevant,

22:09.262 --> 22:12.680
the court will allow the jury
to hear it repeated.

22:12.765 --> 22:13.597
You may proceed.

22:13.716 --> 22:15.299
Well, thank you,
your honor.

22:15.885 --> 22:17.385
[ grunts ]

22:17.470 --> 22:20.388
before he left chicago,
did you caution your son

22:20.473 --> 22:22.940
how to conduct himself
while in mississippi?

22:23.059 --> 22:24.775
Yes, sir.
Well...

22:24.894 --> 22:29.313
Now, I have a -- a paper here
where you are quoted.

22:29.399 --> 22:31.315
Listen carefully,
it says --

22:31.401 --> 22:35.736
"I -- I told him several times
before he left for mississippi

22:35.822 --> 22:40.458
that he should kneel on
the street and beg forgiveness

22:40.576 --> 22:44.628
if he ever insulted
a white man or a white woman."

22:47.083 --> 22:50.217
now...

22:50.303 --> 22:52.920
Did you, uh,
say that to him?

22:53.005 --> 22:54.388
Not those exact words.

22:54.490 --> 22:56.457
Then what did
you tell him?

22:56.559 --> 22:58.459
Well, I told him he would
have to be very careful

22:58.561 --> 23:00.394
with how he spoke,

23:00.463 --> 23:04.215
to always remember to say
"yes, sir," and "no, ma'am."

23:04.250 --> 23:06.267
and if ever there was
an incident that would arise

23:06.302 --> 23:07.802
that might be any trouble

23:07.837 --> 23:09.937
of any kind
with white people --

23:09.972 --> 23:13.541
um, if he bumped into somebody
on the street, for example,

23:13.576 --> 23:15.943
I told him to go ahead
and humble himself.

23:15.962 --> 23:19.447
Did you specifically indicate
to him and caution him

23:19.482 --> 23:20.881
not to do anything
to a white man

23:20.917 --> 23:22.416
so as not to bring on
any trouble?

23:22.452 --> 23:23.517
Yes, sir.

23:23.553 --> 23:24.785
Now, while he was living there
in chicago,

23:24.821 --> 23:26.287
had he been doing anything
to cause you

23:26.322 --> 23:27.788
to give him
that special instruction?

23:27.824 --> 23:31.792
No, sir. Emmett has never been
in any trouble at any time.

23:31.827 --> 23:33.761
And he had never been
in a reform school?

23:33.830 --> 23:34.662
No, sir.

23:34.697 --> 23:36.163
And he had never had
any trouble

23:36.199 --> 23:37.431
in any way
with any white people?

23:37.500 --> 23:39.967
No, sir.

23:40.002 --> 23:41.702
Now, your honor, we submit
that the testimony

23:41.771 --> 23:42.937
is indeed relevant

23:42.972 --> 23:45.039
and that the witness
be permitted to repeat it

23:45.074 --> 23:46.207
in the presence
of the jury.

23:46.242 --> 23:48.042
The prior objections
to this portion

23:48.077 --> 23:49.677
of the testimony
will be sustained,

23:49.712 --> 23:52.713
and the testimony will not
be permitted before the jury.

23:52.815 --> 23:55.566
No further questions,
your honor.

23:55.685 --> 23:57.101
You may step down.

23:57.186 --> 24:04.442
♪♪

24:04.527 --> 24:11.832
♪♪

24:11.918 --> 24:13.451
the state rests.

24:13.536 --> 24:14.869
Your honor, the defense
would like to call

24:14.954 --> 24:18.622
its first witness,
sheriff h.C. Strider.

24:20.126 --> 24:21.208
Hicks: We think the sheriff's
just trying

24:21.294 --> 24:22.543
to keep them
from talking,

24:22.628 --> 24:25.346
but if you agree to verify
your husband's identity,

24:25.431 --> 24:27.131
along with too tight,

24:27.216 --> 24:29.800
we could get authorities
to grant you access to the jail

24:29.886 --> 24:32.052
and allies to protect you.

24:32.155 --> 24:34.922
You said you were a friend
of too tight's.

24:34.957 --> 24:36.190
Ma'am, if your husband

24:36.225 --> 24:38.025
was a witness
to emmett till's murder,

24:38.060 --> 24:41.028
there are probably a lot
of people who want him dead.

24:41.063 --> 24:42.396
Okay, now, the fact that
he's still alive

24:42.431 --> 24:44.198
means there's still a chance
to save him.

24:44.267 --> 24:46.350
[ sighs ]

24:46.435 --> 24:49.737
henry is a good guy.

24:49.772 --> 24:52.773
If he was mixed up in anything
with that boy,

24:52.808 --> 24:54.475
it's because
he had no choice.

24:54.577 --> 24:56.110
We know.

24:56.145 --> 24:57.411
That's why we want to make sure
that the men

24:57.446 --> 25:00.347
who are responsible
are held accountable.

25:07.689 --> 25:09.690
Breland: As sheriff of
tallahatchie county,

25:09.792 --> 25:10.908
have you taken bodies
out of that river

25:10.993 --> 25:11.992
during the summer period,

25:12.078 --> 25:13.077
with weather like we had
here in August?

25:13.162 --> 25:15.195
I have.
And what is your opinion,

25:15.298 --> 25:17.915
based on your past experience,
as to how long

25:18.000 --> 25:19.466
that body
had been in that river?

25:19.552 --> 25:21.502
We object to that, your honor.
He is not a doctor,

25:21.587 --> 25:24.205
and he is not qualified
to testify about that.

25:24.307 --> 25:28.842
He is not qualified as a doctor,
but I think he is qualified.

25:28.928 --> 25:30.427
Overruled.

25:30.513 --> 25:33.347
I would say at least 10 days,
if not 15.

25:33.382 --> 25:34.982
And when the body
was discovered,

25:35.017 --> 25:36.350
how long had it been
since

25:36.385 --> 25:37.818
emmett till
was reported missing?

25:37.887 --> 25:38.986
Three days.

25:39.021 --> 25:40.454
Could you tell whether this was
a white person

25:40.489 --> 25:41.739
or a colored person?

25:41.791 --> 25:43.390
The only way you might able
to tell

25:43.426 --> 25:45.426
it was a colored person
would be the hair,

25:45.461 --> 25:47.695
and I have seen white people
have kinky hair.

25:47.730 --> 25:50.264
And was this body
recognizable to be

25:50.299 --> 25:52.933
that of
any particular person?

25:52.969 --> 25:57.371
Well, if one of my own boys
had been missing,

25:57.406 --> 25:58.839
I really don't think
I could say

25:58.874 --> 26:01.108
whether it was
my son or not.

26:01.177 --> 26:03.677
Or anyone else's.

26:03.746 --> 26:05.679
I couldn't tell that.

26:05.715 --> 26:07.448
All I could tell...

26:07.550 --> 26:09.500
It was a human being.

26:09.585 --> 26:11.252
Your witness.

26:19.929 --> 26:21.478
Mr. Strider,

26:21.597 --> 26:25.399
there was a death certificate
prepared for emmett till,

26:25.484 --> 26:27.818
was there not?
That's right.

26:27.937 --> 26:31.438
And I believe
that you signed

26:31.524 --> 26:33.240
that death certificate,
did you not?

26:33.326 --> 26:34.441
Yes, sir.

26:34.527 --> 26:37.278
And this death certificate
certified the fact

26:37.363 --> 26:39.813
that this body
was that of emmett till,

26:39.915 --> 26:42.649
isn't that correct?
No.

26:42.752 --> 26:45.652
I did not certify
it was emmett till.

26:45.755 --> 26:47.788
I said it was
a dead body.

26:47.873 --> 26:49.590
I never seen emmett till.

26:49.675 --> 26:51.208
I could not swear
it was emmett till

26:51.294 --> 26:53.827
because I didn't know
what he looked like.

26:53.929 --> 26:57.681
♪♪

26:57.800 --> 27:02.336
sheriff, have you made
any investigation to find out

27:02.438 --> 27:03.837
whose body that was?

27:03.939 --> 27:06.774
Who that person was?

27:06.859 --> 27:08.175
I sure have.

27:08.277 --> 27:11.378
What efforts have you made
to find out who that body was?

27:11.480 --> 27:14.398
Well, I got reports
of a negro

27:14.483 --> 27:16.850
who disappeared
over at lambert.

27:16.952 --> 27:19.069
I went over there,
investigated that,

27:19.155 --> 27:22.189
and one man'd tell you
he saw him,

27:22.291 --> 27:23.240
and another man'd tell you

27:23.326 --> 27:25.626
that someone told him
that they saw him,

27:25.711 --> 27:26.994
and then somebody else'd
tell you

27:27.079 --> 27:29.129
that somebody else
knew something about it,

27:29.215 --> 27:31.999
and you'd just end up
right back where you started.

27:32.084 --> 27:34.468
But you have no information
whatsoever to indicate

27:34.553 --> 27:36.637
whose body that was?

27:36.722 --> 27:42.042
You have not gotten
<i> any</i> information about that?

27:42.144 --> 27:44.144
♪♪

27:44.230 --> 27:46.063
no, I have not.

27:46.182 --> 27:53.270
♪♪

27:53.356 --> 27:55.272
so she agreed to go
to the jail?

27:55.358 --> 27:58.242
Mm-hmm.
As long we can
get her in safely.

27:58.361 --> 27:59.743
Which is where you come in.

27:59.862 --> 28:02.413
We need you to go
to chatham again.

28:02.531 --> 28:03.747
Get him to authorize
a search

28:03.866 --> 28:05.399
while there's still time
to introduce new witnesses.

28:05.501 --> 28:06.750
The prosecution rested.

28:06.869 --> 28:08.919
They've already moved on
to the defense.

28:09.038 --> 28:12.089
[ sighs ]
okay, uh...

28:12.208 --> 28:13.257
We need to try anyway.

28:13.376 --> 28:15.008
The judge could make
an exception.

28:15.094 --> 28:16.794
We're talking about
two potential eyewitnesses

28:16.879 --> 28:18.379
to the actual murder.

28:18.464 --> 28:20.764
We just need someone
to bring them in.

28:23.219 --> 28:24.918
I'm sorry that you
and your compatriots

28:25.020 --> 28:26.804
went to all that trouble,
mr. Packton,

28:26.922 --> 28:30.124
but those men are not
in the charleston jail.

28:30.159 --> 28:31.308
What?
How do you know?

28:31.343 --> 28:34.094
Because I took it upon myself
to have it searched,

28:34.130 --> 28:35.996
along with the jail
in sunflower county,

28:36.031 --> 28:37.765
right after I received
the letter you passed along

28:37.833 --> 28:38.899
from dr. Howard.

28:38.934 --> 28:40.901
You suspected
they were being held?

28:40.936 --> 28:45.038
No, but there was mention
of two men named levi collins

28:45.074 --> 28:46.974
and henry lee loggins
and that they were missing,

28:47.009 --> 28:48.809
so I didn't want to leave
any stone unturned.

28:48.844 --> 28:50.778
Both searches, however,
came up empty,

28:50.813 --> 28:52.246
according to
my investigators,

28:52.281 --> 28:53.914
and both sheriffs
raised hell about it.

28:53.949 --> 28:57.334
But if the men were being
held under false names,

28:57.369 --> 28:58.886
how can you be sure
they weren't there?

28:58.921 --> 29:01.922
Loggins' wife should still
be allowed to check.

29:02.024 --> 29:04.391
My investigators
are thorough,

29:04.427 --> 29:06.226
and butting heads
with sheriff strider again

29:06.262 --> 29:08.762
is not going to do
my case any good.

29:08.798 --> 29:10.431
Thank you for coming in.

29:10.499 --> 29:13.133
[ tense music plays ]

29:13.202 --> 29:19.039
♪♪

29:19.141 --> 29:22.676
you know, if this really is
the last case of your career,

29:22.762 --> 29:24.061
you sure you'll be able
to live with yourself,

29:24.180 --> 29:25.596
knowing that you might have let
the only witnesses

29:25.681 --> 29:28.649
to the crime
slip right through your fingers?

29:28.751 --> 29:43.096
♪♪
breland: Mrs. Bryant,
I direct your attention

29:43.165 --> 29:44.731
to Wednesday night,
the 24th of August.

29:44.834 --> 29:46.633
Who was in the store
with you that night?

29:46.719 --> 29:47.968
Chatham: If the court pleases,
we object

29:48.053 --> 29:49.720
to anything that happened
on that evening

29:49.839 --> 29:52.239
unless it is connected
to the crime in question,

29:52.341 --> 29:55.342
which began on Sunday morning,
the 28th.

29:55.427 --> 29:57.094
Well, we will connect it.

30:01.684 --> 30:03.350
The court would ask the jury
to retire

30:03.435 --> 30:04.985
to the jury room
for a moment.

30:05.070 --> 30:08.121
[ chairs sliding, shuffling ]

30:22.254 --> 30:25.873
now, the court will permit both
sides to address the question

30:25.958 --> 30:27.140
as to whether or not
this testimony

30:27.243 --> 30:29.409
will be permissible
before the jury.

30:29.512 --> 30:32.846
[ clears throat ]
your honor, the state argued

30:32.932 --> 30:34.848
that one of the men
who came to the home

30:34.934 --> 30:37.768
of mose wright on August 28th
wanted to see the boy

30:37.887 --> 30:39.186
who did the talking at money.

30:39.271 --> 30:42.222
Now, the state raised inferences
which the defendants believe

30:42.308 --> 30:46.259
they are entitled to explain
and to show what happened.

30:46.362 --> 30:49.112
And further, we believe that
these occurrences are a part

30:49.231 --> 30:52.366
of what the state alleges
is one entire transaction --

30:52.451 --> 30:54.768
the beginning and the inception
of the incident.

30:54.870 --> 30:57.404
And as much, the occurrences
there on that occasion

30:57.489 --> 30:58.939
are a part of
the<i> res gestae --</i>

30:59.041 --> 31:01.825
the circumstances --
which relate to the case.

31:01.911 --> 31:03.493
And as such, the defendants
should be permitted

31:03.579 --> 31:06.463
to offer testimony
in that particular.

31:06.582 --> 31:09.750
Chatham: Our proof started
with the occurrences

31:09.785 --> 31:12.152
early Sunday morning,
when two or more persons

31:12.187 --> 31:14.888
came to mose wright's house
to get the boy.

31:14.924 --> 31:17.457
We offered no proof
of anything prior,

31:17.493 --> 31:20.527
and mrs. Bryant wasn't brought
into this whatsoever.

31:20.563 --> 31:22.162
And I think I can say that

31:22.197 --> 31:25.065
her name was never
mentioned in this case.

31:25.100 --> 31:26.633
Your honor, the supreme court
of mississippi

31:26.669 --> 31:28.769
has many times held
that former difficulties

31:28.804 --> 31:31.138
between parties cannot be
brought in as evidence.

31:31.173 --> 31:33.774
And further, we contend that
anything that happened

31:33.809 --> 31:36.276
down there is no justification
for murder anyway.

31:36.312 --> 31:39.313
Your honor, I would like
to call attention to the fact

31:39.398 --> 31:41.398
that the supreme court
has ruled

31:41.517 --> 31:43.984
that an incident
may be separated by days,

31:44.069 --> 31:47.387
and by weeks even, but if they
can be connected as part

31:47.489 --> 31:49.523
or partial
of a man's transaction,

31:49.608 --> 31:50.941
then it doesn't mean
that these things

31:51.026 --> 31:53.076
must all happen
right together.

31:54.780 --> 31:56.363
[ clears throat ]

31:58.751 --> 32:01.168
gentlemen, the court is of
the opinion

32:01.270 --> 32:02.603
that the testimony
being offered here

32:02.705 --> 32:06.106
pertains to an incident
prior to the crime in question.

32:06.208 --> 32:08.342
Therefore, it is
not admissible for the jury.

32:08.427 --> 32:11.461
[ crowd murmuring ]

32:14.183 --> 32:15.382
[ murmuring quiets ]

32:15.467 --> 32:16.883
breland: Your honor, we still
would like to develop

32:16.969 --> 32:19.386
this testimony
for the sake of the record.

32:22.391 --> 32:24.641
The court will allow it,
for the sake of the record,

32:24.727 --> 32:27.027
not for the jury.

32:27.112 --> 32:29.646
You may proceed.

32:29.732 --> 32:31.148
Mrs. Bryant,

32:31.233 --> 32:34.451
on Wednesday evening,
the 24th day of August, 1955,

32:34.570 --> 32:38.789
did an incident occur
which made an impression on you?

32:38.907 --> 32:40.807
Yes.

32:40.909 --> 32:43.493
And just tell the court
what happened there at the time,

32:43.579 --> 32:45.245
please, ma'am.

32:47.299 --> 32:48.915
This nigger man
came in the store

32:49.001 --> 32:50.950
and stopped there
at the candy case.

32:51.053 --> 32:52.786
Now, when this negro man
came in the store,

32:52.888 --> 32:54.120
where were you in the store?

32:54.223 --> 32:57.758
I was farther back in the store,
behind the counter.

32:57.843 --> 33:00.594
Now, what transpired up there
at the candy counter?

33:03.482 --> 33:04.798
I asked him
what he wanted.

33:04.900 --> 33:06.400
And did he tell you?
Yes.

33:06.485 --> 33:08.185
And after you got
the merchandise for him,

33:08.270 --> 33:09.186
what did you do?

33:09.271 --> 33:10.988
I held out my hand
for his money.

33:11.106 --> 33:13.073
And which hand
did you hold out?

33:13.158 --> 33:14.324
My right hand.

33:14.443 --> 33:16.910
Will you show the court
how you held your hand out?

33:21.083 --> 33:22.699
And did he give you
the money?

33:25.337 --> 33:28.255
No.
What did he do?

33:28.323 --> 33:29.723
He caught my hand.

33:29.758 --> 33:30.691
[ crowd murmuring ]

33:30.726 --> 33:32.125
[ gavel bangs ]

33:32.194 --> 33:34.494
[ murmuring quiets ]

33:34.563 --> 33:36.096
now, will you, uh --
will you show the court

33:36.131 --> 33:37.631
how he grasped your hand?

33:38.734 --> 33:40.834
[ crowd murmuring ]

33:40.869 --> 33:42.903
and was that a-a strong grip
or a light grip

33:42.938 --> 33:45.238
he had when he, uh,
held your hand?

33:45.274 --> 33:46.707
A strong grip.

33:46.809 --> 33:47.674
Hmm.

33:47.743 --> 33:48.909
How'd you get loose?

33:48.944 --> 33:51.678
Well, I-I jerked it loose,
like this.

33:51.714 --> 33:54.498
[ crowd murmuring,
gavel banging ]

33:54.533 --> 33:57.317
quiet! Quiet!

33:57.352 --> 33:59.286
And was it with that much
difficulty that you --

33:59.354 --> 34:00.220
that you got loose?

34:00.289 --> 34:01.705
Yes.

34:01.740 --> 34:03.790
[ inhales deeply ]

34:03.826 --> 34:09.196
and just what did he say
when he grabbed your hand?

34:09.231 --> 34:12.232
He said, "how about a date,
baby?"

34:12.267 --> 34:13.166
[ crowd murmuring ]

34:13.202 --> 34:14.601
quiet!
[ gavel banging ]

34:14.636 --> 34:16.436
quiet!
Chatham: Your honor!

34:16.472 --> 34:19.389
Your honor!

34:19.425 --> 34:20.357
That is enough.

34:20.409 --> 34:23.210
[ gavel banging ]

34:23.278 --> 34:24.711
that's enough.

34:24.747 --> 34:26.363
[ crowd murmuring quietly ]

34:30.085 --> 34:33.420
and when you freed yourself,
what did you do then?

34:36.125 --> 34:39.009
Well, I turned and tried to get
to the back of the store,

34:39.128 --> 34:43.180
but he came at me
and caught me by the register.

34:43.298 --> 34:47.467
Mrs. Bryant,
will you stand up

34:47.553 --> 34:51.772
and put my hands
just where he grasped you?

34:51.857 --> 34:54.357
Will --
will you show the court?

34:54.476 --> 34:57.360
[ suspenseful music plays ]

34:57.479 --> 35:02.983
♪♪

35:03.068 --> 35:08.572
♪♪

35:08.657 --> 35:10.540
[ crowd murmuring,
gavel banging ]

35:10.659 --> 35:12.409
order!

35:12.494 --> 35:14.244
In other words,
with his, uh --

35:14.329 --> 35:17.798
his left arm
around your back?

35:17.883 --> 35:22.836
A-and his right hand
on your hip?
[ crowd murmuring ]

35:22.921 --> 35:24.087
[ gavel bangs ]

35:24.173 --> 35:25.639
order.

35:25.724 --> 35:27.040
Yes.

35:27.142 --> 35:28.875
Uh-huh.

35:28.977 --> 35:30.677
Um...

35:30.762 --> 35:31.878
♪♪

35:31.980 --> 35:33.480
please.

35:33.565 --> 35:43.106
♪♪

35:43.192 --> 35:47.577
and did he say anything to you
at that time

35:47.696 --> 35:50.063
when he grabbed you there?

35:50.165 --> 35:51.198
Yes.

35:51.283 --> 35:54.034
He said, "what's the matter,
baby?

35:54.119 --> 35:56.837
Can't you take it?"

35:56.872 --> 35:57.904
he said, "what's the matter,
baby?

35:57.973 --> 35:59.840
Can't you take it?"

35:59.942 --> 36:02.475
yes.

36:02.511 --> 36:05.645
And did you then
try to free yourself?

36:05.714 --> 36:07.046
Yes.
And was it difficult?

36:07.065 --> 36:09.349
Did you succeed
in freeing yourself?

36:09.418 --> 36:10.500
[voice breaking] yes.

36:10.536 --> 36:13.119
And did he say anything further
to you at that time?

36:13.155 --> 36:15.322
Yes. He said...
[ sobs ]

36:15.390 --> 36:18.558
"you needn't
be afraid of me."

36:18.594 --> 36:23.230
and -- and did he then use, uh,
language that you don't use?

36:23.298 --> 36:24.531
Yes.
Hmm.

36:24.566 --> 36:29.569
And can you tell the court
what that word begins with --

36:29.605 --> 36:31.838
what letter it begins with?

36:31.907 --> 36:34.774
♪♪

36:34.810 --> 36:37.510
oh, in other words,
it is an unprintable word?

36:37.579 --> 36:39.679
♪♪

36:39.748 --> 36:40.981
yes.

36:41.016 --> 36:44.150
And did he say anything after
that one unprintable word?

36:44.219 --> 36:46.086
♪♪

36:46.121 --> 36:48.521
yes, he said, well...

36:48.590 --> 36:50.223
[ sobs ]

36:50.292 --> 36:52.342
"with white women before."

36:52.427 --> 36:54.361
[ crowd murmuring ]

36:54.396 --> 36:56.196
something to the effect
that he had been

36:56.265 --> 36:58.731
with white women before?

36:58.834 --> 37:01.301
Yes.

37:01.336 --> 37:04.871
And after you, uh,
freed yourself from him,

37:04.907 --> 37:06.289
what did you do then?

37:06.375 --> 37:08.441
♪♪

37:08.477 --> 37:10.877
well, this other nigger came in
and grabbed him by the arm

37:10.913 --> 37:13.246
and told him to "come on,"
and, "let's go."

37:13.282 --> 37:15.615
did he go, uh,
willingly or unwillingly?

37:15.667 --> 37:17.517
Unwillingly.

37:17.552 --> 37:19.286
And did he say
anything further to you

37:19.321 --> 37:23.490
after he had said
these obscene remarks?

37:23.525 --> 37:26.860
Yes. He turned and said,
"goodbye."

37:26.895 --> 37:28.561
and what did you do then?

37:28.597 --> 37:32.232
I ran out the door
to go to the car.

37:32.267 --> 37:33.867
Which car?
Mrs. Milam's.

37:33.902 --> 37:35.101
And what did you go
to the car for?

37:35.137 --> 37:36.303
To get the pistol.

37:36.338 --> 37:37.220
Crowd: That's right!
Yeah!

37:37.306 --> 37:38.605
[ gavel bangs ]

37:38.640 --> 37:40.340
[ indistinct conversations ]

37:40.409 --> 37:42.726
[ gavel bangs ]

37:42.761 --> 37:45.161
[ clears throat ]

37:45.197 --> 37:46.579
as you went through the door
and went to the car,

37:46.615 --> 37:48.715
did you see
this man again?

37:48.784 --> 37:50.050
Yes.

37:50.118 --> 37:54.220
And did he say or do
anything at that time?

37:54.289 --> 37:56.790
[weakly] he whistled.

37:56.825 --> 38:00.060
Can you make a sound
something like the whistle

38:00.128 --> 38:02.028
he made there?

38:02.097 --> 38:02.963
Hmm?

38:02.998 --> 38:04.698
Well, was it something
like this?

38:04.733 --> 38:06.032
[ wolf whistles ]

38:06.101 --> 38:08.234
[ crowd groans ]

38:08.303 --> 38:09.970
yes.

38:10.005 --> 38:12.088
After you got
your pistol, mrs. Bryant,

38:12.174 --> 38:13.206
where was this boy then?

38:13.241 --> 38:16.710
Or I should say --
where was this<i> man?</i>

38:16.745 --> 38:19.179
When I turned around,
he was getting in a car

38:19.247 --> 38:21.381
down the road.

38:21.450 --> 38:22.849
Mrs. Bryant...

38:22.884 --> 38:25.635
♪♪

38:25.687 --> 38:28.588
...What sort of impression
did this occurrence make on you?

38:28.657 --> 38:31.358
♪♪

38:31.393 --> 38:33.159
I was just
scared to death.

38:33.261 --> 38:36.463
♪♪

38:36.498 --> 38:39.466
your honor, we submit
the testimony's relevant

38:39.501 --> 38:42.302
to remove from the minds
of the jury the impression

38:42.337 --> 38:44.971
that nothing but talk
had occurred in money.

38:45.040 --> 38:49.042
♪♪

38:49.111 --> 38:52.045
it remains the opinion
of this court

38:52.080 --> 38:54.447
that the evidence
is not admissible.

38:54.483 --> 38:56.950
Therefore...
[ crowd murmuring ]

38:56.985 --> 38:59.519
I will have order!

38:59.554 --> 39:03.757
Therefore, the jury will not
hear this testimony.

39:03.825 --> 39:04.724
[ crowd murmuring ]

39:04.826 --> 39:06.626
[ gavel banging ]

39:06.695 --> 39:08.528
[ indistinct conversations ]

39:08.597 --> 39:10.013
that's enough.

39:10.132 --> 39:16.619
♪♪

39:16.738 --> 39:30.400
♪♪
mamie:
How dare that woman!

39:30.485 --> 39:32.235
How dare she swear on
a holy bible to tell the truth,

39:32.320 --> 39:36.156
only to -- to spout horrific
lies about a child!

39:36.241 --> 39:38.625
A child that she knows
is dead because of her!

39:38.710 --> 39:41.127
A child they strategically
referred to as a "man."

39:41.213 --> 39:43.747
those lawyers never even
showed her a picture of bo.

39:43.832 --> 39:45.415
That was deliberate.
On one hand,

39:45.500 --> 39:47.167
bryant and milam
claim they let him go

39:47.252 --> 39:48.501
because it wasn't the boy
from the store.

39:48.587 --> 39:50.470
On the other hand,
the wife says it was,

39:50.555 --> 39:52.205
so he deserved
what he got.

39:52.307 --> 39:53.206
It doesn't make sense.

39:53.308 --> 39:55.975
None of it does.

39:56.061 --> 39:58.762
Every word of it
was a lie!

39:58.847 --> 40:01.181
And -- and the whistling,
on top of everything else!

40:01.266 --> 40:04.484
My -- my son would never whistle
at a white woman.

40:04.569 --> 40:05.902
I taught him better.

40:06.021 --> 40:06.986
At least the judge
kept the jury

40:07.072 --> 40:09.689
from hearing
those theatrics.

40:09.775 --> 40:14.861
The only reason he would whistle
is because of his stutter.

40:14.946 --> 40:18.198
I taught him to do that
if he got stuck on a word.

40:18.283 --> 40:20.583
So even if he did whistle,

40:20.702 --> 40:22.752
he wouldn't have been
whistling at her.

40:22.871 --> 40:25.455
Sweetheart, what difference
does it make?

40:25.540 --> 40:28.007
It still doesn't justify
what they did to him.

40:31.880 --> 40:35.098
I tried so hard to say
the right things in there

40:35.217 --> 40:37.600
and to act the right way.

40:37.719 --> 40:40.419
None of it even mattered,
did it?

40:40.522 --> 40:42.472
Nothing I said could have
changed a thing,

40:42.557 --> 40:45.308
because they were
never going to listen.

40:46.445 --> 40:48.394
And I was a fool to hope
that they would.

40:48.480 --> 40:51.197
♪♪

